09/08/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- A notorious criminal, Dritan Dajti, killed four police officers and one civilian in the port city of Durres on Friday (August 7th) during a police operation aimed at arresting him. 
At least six were injured in the incident. 
Local media reported Dajti, 32, was also hurt and has been taken to a Tirana military hospital. 
Albania observed a day of national mourning on Saturday to commemorate the four killed policemen. 
Daiti is wanted by Interpol for murders and drug smuggling. 
(Balkanweb, Lajme, Telegrafi, RTV21, Kosova-Sot, AP, Xinhua, Makfax, MIA, BTA, Makfax - 07/08/09)
